<Content>OK for price We stayed at Comfort Inn Boston as the cost was reasonable in comparison to most Boston hotels. The hotel sent a complementary shuttle bus to pick us up from the airport, which was really helpful. The hotel room was clean and comfortable. I had no difficulty with internet wireless access on my laptop in the hotel and this was complementary. Breakfast was included in cost also, which consisted of fresh waffles, muffins, bread, coffee, yogurt, fruit juice etc. I thought that this was good value as other 'better hotels' had charged us for all of the above, additional to our room rate, and the service was no better than the Comfort Inn Boston. On the downside, it is hard to believe that this hotel is advertised as part of a complex containing restaurants. It is a shorter walk to Dunkin' Donuts and the supermarket opposite the hotel than to the 'restaurants' on-site. There is a railway behind the hotel and though I occasionally heard some noise, it wasn't bad enough to cause any great problems. 
