<Content>For the money, well worth it We stayed here 27-31/10/03. The hotel is fairly typical travelodge affair. Rooms were clean and functional. Two adults and two kids. Breafast was OK and part of the deal, which as you are out and about seeing Boston was OK. The shuttle bus is good and free, takes you to the local tube/subway station, about 5 mins away. The cost into town is only $1 each person.If you are arriving by train, get off at South Station, then the red line outboard to JFK, two stops. If you fly in, the hotel will pick you up for free from the aiport. Just ring them when your plane gets in, about 15 mins away.Overall, good value for money, beware though, you can get very odd deals, so shop around. We were quoted $450 inc taxes for the 4 nights on US sites, however, we found a bucket site in the UK which did it for $270 inc taxes. 
